Original: As you proceed through the forest of
illusions, map in hand, you sense
a presence past the thicket up ahead.
[Page]
When you cautiously peek through the
branches, you see a shadowy monster
with its back turned to you.
[Page]
If there is anyone in your party
skilled at ambushes or sniping,
you could try attacking the monster.
Translation: As you proceed through the forest of
illusions, map in hand, you sense
a presence past the thicket up ahead.
[Page]
When you cautiously peek through the
branches, you see a shadowy monster
with its back turned to you.
[Page]
If there is anyone in your party
skilled at ambushes or sniping,
you could try attacking the monster.

Original: [Color:5]Attack the monster?[Color:0]
Translation: [Color:5]Attack the monster?[Color:0]

Original: [Color:5]Who will attack?[Color:0]
Translation: [Color:5]Who will attack?[Color:0]

Original: [Character:0] peers into the thicket to
prepare an ambush, but then cries out
for the party to look behind them!
Translation: [Character:0] peers into the thicket to
prepare an ambush, but then cries out
for the party to look behind them!

Original: You quickly turn and see that a horde
of monsters has surrounded you!
[Page]
It seems the shadow in the thicket
was a ruse formed by a spell!
[Page]
Luckily, the monsters panic to see you
penetrate their ruse and you catch
them off guard as you enter battle!
Translation: You quickly turn and see that a horde

[Page]

Original: Weapon at the ready, [Character:0]
attacks the shadowy fiend!
[Page]

strike naught but air, you realize
that you have fallen into a trap!
[Page]
Too late, you deduce that the shadow
in the thicket was a ruse formed by
a spell!

Original: Unfortunately, you have no chance to
brace yourselves as the monsters
launch their attack!
Translation: Unfortunately, you have no chance to

launch their attack!

Original: Thanks to your ally versed in sensing
nearby presences, you handily deal
with the crisis.
[Page]
You thank your guildmate for their
meritorious deeds and resume your
walk down the forest path...
Translation: Thanks to your ally versed in sensing

Original: Seeing a monster so defenseless seems
unnatural, and you elect not to get
involved.
Translation: Seeing a monster so defenseless seems

Original: As you journey through the mist-
choked maze, you eventually reach
the end of an open area.
[Page]
There, you see a large leaf jutting
out. A steady drip of water from above
is pooling in it.
[Page]
If you wish to quench your thirst,
this is a perfect opportunity, though
there is only water enough for one.
Translation: As you journey through the mist-
choked maze, you eventually reach
the end of an open area.
[Page]
There, you see a large leaf jutting
out. A steady drip of water from above
is pooling in it.
[Page]
If you wish to quench your thirst,
this is a perfect opportunity, though
there is only water enough for one.

Original: You find a large leaf jutting from a
corner, collecting water that drips
steadily from above.
[Page]
There seems to be only water enough
for one, but if you wish to quench
your thirst, you are free to do so.
Translation: You find a large leaf jutting from a
corner, collecting water that drips
steadily from above.
[Page]
There seems to be only water enough
for one, but if you wish to quench
your thirst, you are free to do so.

Original: [Color:5]Drink the water?[Color:0]
Translation: [Color:5]Drink the water?[Color:0]

Translation: [Color:5]Who will drink it?[Color:0]

Original: [Character:0] raises the leaf, tips it, and
gulps down the pooled water.
[Page]
[Character:0]'s passion for the adventure
is rekindled!
Translation: [Character:0] raises the leaf, tips it, and
gulps down the pooled water.
[Page]

Original: It may be dangerous to stop here even
for a short time... You change your
mind and continue your travels.
Translation: It may be dangerous to stop here even

Original: As you proceed through the thick mist
of the forest, you hear high-pitched
chirping at a dead end.
[Page]
Looking toward the sound, you see a
bird's nest in the trees. An adorably
plump chick is warbling inside.
[Page]
After gazing at the chick for a while,
your heart feels rested. Satisfied,
you go back the way you came.
Translation: As you proceed through the thick mist

chirping at a dead end.
[Page]

bird's nest in the trees. An adorably
plump chick is warbling inside.
[Page]

Original: You hear the chirping of a chick

Translation: You hear the chirping of a chick
